<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-11T01:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-11T01:54:00-05:00" n="871" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1915: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-11T10:00:00+03:06">August 11,
                                    1943—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>88. For Murray<note n="8" xml:id="d871fn8">Wallace Murray, Adviser an
                                Political Relations.</note> and Alling.<note n="9" xml:id="d871fn9">Paul H. Alling, Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                                Affairs.</note> Referring to verbal message delivered by
                                Hoskins.<note n="10" xml:id="d871fn10">Lt. Col. Harold B. Hoskins;
                                regarding the visit by Lt. Col. Hoskins to Saudi Arabia, see <ref target="#pg_790">pp. 790</ref>–<ref target="#pg_821">821</ref>,
                                    <hi rend="italic">passim</hi>.</note> Still adhere to opinion
                            expressed in Department that Dhahran is preferable location.<note n="11" xml:id="d871fn11">i.e., for a U.S. Consulate in Saudi Arabia.</note>
                            While there is no precedent to use for guidance I see no reason to
                            anticipate objection by local authorities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>